header.gameNote: MAC MEN'S TOURNAMENT - QUARTERFINALS AT CLEVELAND OH

article.headline: Ball St. 76, Ohio 73
article.story: CLEVELAND -- Tyrae Robinson's basket with 2 minutes remaining in overtime put Ball State ahead for good and gave the Cardinals a 76-73 win over Ohio in the quarterfinals of the Mid-American Conference tournament on Thursday night. Jesse Berry scored 20 points to lead Ball State (19-12), which scored the last nine points of regulation to tie the score with the defending tournament champions. Ball State, the tournament's fourth seed, faces top-seeded Kent State in the semifinals Friday night. Second-seeded Western Michigan meets sixth-seeded Akron in the other semifinal. D.J. Cooper and DeVaughn Washington led fifth-seeded Ohio (18-15) with 19 points apiece. Randy Davis' 3-pointer with 3:22 left in overtime gave Ball State a 71-68 lead, but Nick Kellogg's three-point play tied it with 2:17 to play. Robinson's basket in the lane put Ball State up for good.
